1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Did you know how the way you produce information changes your memory?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,600
It's called the production effect, and it's more powerful than you think.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:15,200
When you read, write, or say information aloud, your brain locks it in better.

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:19,600
Research shows that producing information enhances recall, especially in learning environments.

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:23,600
So next time you study, try saying it out loud.

6
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,000
It could make all the difference.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,800
Want to learn more about memory tricks?

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:30,000
Follow for tips!
